FILE - In this March 29, 2018 file photo, President Donald Trump poses for members of the media with then White House Communications Director Hope Hicks on her last day before he boards Marine One on the South Lawn of the White House in Washington.
Hicks, one of President Donald Trump's most trusted and longest-serving aides, is returning to the White House.
(AP Photo/Andrew Harnik)FILE - In this March 29, 2018 file photo, President Donald Trump poses for members of the media with then White House Communications Director Hope Hicks on her last day before he boards Marine One on the South Lawn of the White House in Washington.
Hicks, one of President Donald Trump's most trusted and longest-serving aides, is returning to the White House.
The news of her decision was praised publicly by top administration officials, including Stephanie Grisham, the White House press secretary who also serves as the current White House communications director.